data.name: Cauliflower Biryani
data.description: A fragrant cauliflower biryani with classic spices and fresh herbs.
instructions: Rinse the grain and soak for 1015 minutes. Drain and keep aside.
Heat oil/ghee in a heavy pan. Add cumin and whole spices; saut for 30 seconds.
Add sliced onion and cook until light golden. Add ginger-garlic paste; saut 1 minute.
Add tomatoes, spices, and salt. Cook until tomatoes soften and oil separates.
Add the main protein/vegetables. Cook 46 minutes (or until 70% done).
Add curd, mint, coriander, and lemon juice. Mix well and simmer 2 minutes.
Add soaked grain + measured water. Cover and cook on low until grain is cooked and water is absorbed.
Rest covered 5 minutes. Fluff gently and serve hot.
